</title>
<subSubSection id="F93FB655CE489238345CFF6DB5663CC6" pageId="null" pageNumber="522" type="description">
<paragraph id="3669F9E67F7E9CADC89643D74FB1B1FF" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="1D73D592EBD94E8EF1642754C1920DAA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Buphthalmum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="522" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salicifolium">
<emphasis id="2E37CA3C12CD515A123E43034CEB0E38" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">B. salicifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2) durch folgende Merkmale: 15-45 cm hoch, meist nur kurz behaart (
<emphasis id="FEEECBE4EB91227C2ABEC78571D48DA2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">
Haare kaum 
<normalizedToken id="D1E312A79EF5F9B96FDCDC6AC8700543" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">laenger</normalizedToken>
als 1 mm
</emphasis>
)
<emphasis id="84CE36C63ED3C14B5BB6898D778C0AF7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">
; 
<normalizedToken id="D5887B16D7D036FF0044A1E1F662DFD6" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
in eine lange Spitze ausgezogen;
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="02F9737CD76D4199E876D57679212127" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
zudem 
<normalizedToken id="0478875B459CC259FA8546B0010F6C48" originalValue="dünner" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">duenner</normalizedToken>
und oft auch 
<normalizedToken id="ECF62A093E53AE7D9D8DBCFB8A604EB4" originalValue="schmäler" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">schmaeler</normalizedToken>
; 
<emphasis id="92B005BC6CE008F3DBA9D5783B1F2B64" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicName id="3F42BF8807E968B559276064C7B9D731" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pappus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pappus</taxonomicName>
der innern 
<normalizedToken id="FF4E6D55F261147EC0A270417B168DF8" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
0,4
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="241C50E932E360C7B2F77DFF71478A9A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">1 mm lang.</emphasis>
- 
<normalizedToken id="ACEAED6DE82EE94261786BA89D2DFC2E" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="98BA17113EBD733CB7D81D4B22B64AEA" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis id="94F02EA7B0B9C2AD629DD636687B9FA5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="17FC556106BA6FCB0E2386B504F368F8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">20:</emphasis>
Material aus botanischen 
<normalizedToken id="BAE70717250ED76AF17DBCD754742952" originalValue="Gärten" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Gaerten</normalizedToken>
(Sakai aus Darlington und Wylie 1955).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F8C339FAE8A949317B6F90816BA3199" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis id="44B3A241EB168DFAE144BD74EBBB0C1E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin und montan. Wahrscheinlich wie 
<taxonomicName id="247C24402D728658E6B1CD79E8ED4403" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Buphthalmum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="522" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salicifolium">
<emphasis id="5CBEDDF728EF4ACFBCCCB8B5C94CE553" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">B. salicifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2), in warmen Lagen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C48B81D45130EC419E4FB596BCA8A77" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis id="4326DD1A026040F382D3B3E46CF40BC0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Verbreitung. Westalpin-apenninische Pflanze:</emphasis>
Westalpen, Nordapennin. - Im Gebiet: Savoyen (Bugey?, Gegend von 
<normalizedToken id="FF5E0086F0C229A4F5F72C6AA9EDEE2D" originalValue="Chambéry" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Chambery</normalizedToken>
und das Val 
<normalizedToken id="32CF11418D54EE2A014C3BF9641F7EAC" originalValue="d’Isère" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">d'Isere</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="0A0CE0BA9A752A365040D2DC8E291F82" originalValue="aufwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">aufwaerts</normalizedToken>
in die Tarentaise und in die Maurienne), Valsesia (Valduggia), Valle 
<normalizedToken id="FF753C4A2A742B9904FEDABE83FEAD87" originalValue="d’Ossola" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">d'Ossola</normalizedToken>
(Macugnaga), 
<normalizedToken id="C0E7EFC8A23E0173204FF1E811360B71" originalValue="südliches" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">suedliches</normalizedToken>
Tessin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91AE2ABE6ECFFBFBD2416F2731FCD15F" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis id="1DACCBCC0563EE5DCD318A146C2FD749" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Die von 
<taxonomicName id="A5DA28310B98804C9BFC79C3F788D11F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Buphthalmum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="522" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salicifolium">
<emphasis id="8989FF95320621538B60DA1A2CEB7BAA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">B. salicifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2) nur wenig verschiedene und teilweise durch 
<normalizedToken id="73136E6E60FABC00EDD5AE53DE36E988" originalValue="Übergänge" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">Uebergaenge</normalizedToken>
verbundene Art mu&amp;szlig genauer untersucht werden. Besonders sind konstante Unterschiedsmerkmale 
<normalizedToken id="D9E3DBAF545F1B6A6070E56D492457C6" originalValue="gegenüber" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">gegenueber</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="1F021098A8FA11BE3E8F5B86512F91F9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Buphthalmum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="522" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salicifolium">
<emphasis id="448DE3D1AA8BD2C7A167F16D8D7155E3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="522">B. salicifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und die genaue geographische Verbreitung herauszuarbeiten.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
